      "name": "Hemolysis RH index comparison against clinical pump dataset",
      "description": "CFD-predicted relative hemolysis index (RH) values were compared against hemolysis measurements drawn from a prospective registry of CPB patients across five flow-speed operating points. The observational dataset spans 312 pump-hours and covers the full operating envelope specified in the COU. Agreement between CFD predictions and observed RH values was within ±12% at all five operating points, satisfying the RH < 1 acceptance criterion. The breadth and clinical realism of this dataset are cited as primary justification for model acceptance.",
